%I A397437 #12 Jul 01 2026 19:27:58
%S A397437 1,5,14,33,75,169,380,854,1919,4312,9689,21771,48919,109920,246988,
%T A397437 554977,1247022,2802033,6296111,14147233,31788544,71428210,160497731,
%U A397437 360635128,810339777,1820816951,4091338551,9193154276,20656830152,46415476029,104294627934,234347901745,526574955395
%N A397437 Growth function of the reflection group of a four-dimensional orthoscheme with distinct edge lengths.
%C A397437 A four-dimensional orthoscheme (path simplex) is a simplex with vertices V_0,...,V_4 whose edges V_0V_1, V_1V_2, V_2V_3, V_3V_4 are mutually perpendicular; here the four edge lengths are distinct positive rationals. W is the group generated by the reflections in the five facets, and a(n) is the number of elements of W of word-length n in these reflections.
%C A397437 Two facets are perpendicular exactly when they are non-consecutive, so W is the right-angled Coxeter group with the path Coxeter diagram P_5; its growth series is given by Steinberg's formula, which yields the generating function and recurrence below.
%C A397437 The growth depends only on the perpendicularity pattern, not on the edge lengths. For dimension >= 3 the geometric orbit count equals this abstract growth for any distinct edge lengths (proved in the linked paper, using that distinct lengths force the consecutive dihedral angles irrational). The 2-dimensional analog is the right-triangle reflection group A396406. Verified by direct rational-arithmetic computation on edge lengths (1,2,3,5) through word-length 10.
%H A397437 Vico Bonfioli, <a href="https://github.com/elvec1o/pythagorean-reflection-sequence">The Universal Right-Triangle Reflection Sequence (Unequal Legs)</a>, GitHub repository, 2026.
%H A397437 Vico Bonfioli, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20370090">Data and proofs (Zenodo)</a>, doi:10.5281/zenodo.20370090, 2026.
%H A397437 Vico Bonfioli, <a href="https://github.com/ElVec1o/pythagorean-reflection-sequence/blob/main/paper/journal/paper1b.pdf">Orthoscheme growth and Class C faithfulness</a>, 2026.
%H A397437 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (2,1,-1).
%F A397437 G.f.: (1 + x)^3 / (1 - 2*x - x^2 + x^3).
%F A397437 a(0)=1, a(1)=5, a(2)=14, a(3)=33; a(n) = 2*a(n-1) + a(n-2) - a(n-3) for n >= 4.
%F A397437 a(n+1)/a(n) -> 1 + 2*cos(2*Pi/7) = 2.2469796..., the largest real root of x^3 - 2*x^2 - x + 1.
%e A397437 a(1) = 5: the five reflections in the bounding faces are the 5 elements of word-length 1.
%t A397437 LinearRecurrence[{2, 1, -1}, {1, 5, 14, 33}, 33]
%o A397437 (Python)
%o A397437 def aseq(N):
%o A397437     s = [1, 5, 14, 33]
%o A397437     while len(s) < N:
%o A397437         s.append(2*s[-1] + s[-2] - s[-3])
%o A397437     return s
%o A397437 print(aseq(33))
%Y A397437 Cf. A006054 (same linear recurrence, signature (2,1,-1), and same growth rate 1 + 2*cos(2*Pi/7)).
%Y A397437 Cf. A106805 and A033303 (same g.f. denominator 1 - 2*x - x^2 + x^3, different numerator).
%Y A397437 Cf. A396406 (2D right-triangle reflection sequence, unequal legs).
%Y A397437 Cf. A396927 (5D analog, same orthoscheme family).
%Y A397437 Cf. A008137 (3D all-equal-legs cube corner; affine Weyl group B~_3 growth series).
%K A397437 nonn,easy,new
%O A397437 0,2
